{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:39.560362+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 13f692f414ab9fb9bc397b72a6c13de9db1c8cb6)", "id": "lc_a4c1137d-e008-4609-8009-334a3fc099c2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no\">\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"<%- description %>\">\n    <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\">\n    <title><%- title %></title>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <noscript>\n      <strong>We're sorry but <%- title %> doesn't work properly without JavaScript enabled. Please enable it to continue.</strong>\n    </noscript>\n    <div id=\"app\"></div>\n    <script type=\"module\" src=\"/src/main.js\"></script>\n  </body>\n</html>", "id": "lc_9a95b361-b791-4e1c-b31b-0da358f1ccb1"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "24bf0424-7dc7-41a7-91ec-383b35de4782", "tool_call_id": "call_00_CpK7DGMUl2oe5C1ivoiL7121", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:56.761805+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## How the app bootstraps routing and layout rendering\n\n### 1. Entry point (`src/main.js`)\n\n```js\nimport { createPinia } from 'pinia'\nimport { createApp } from 'vue'\nimport Default from '@/layouts/default/Default.vue'\nimport App from './App.vue'\nimport { router } from './router'\n\nconst app = createApp(App)\n\napp.component('LayoutDefault', Default)   // Global registration → `<LayoutDefault>`\napp.use(createPinia())                    // State management\napp.use(router)                           // Router\n\napp.mount('#app')                         // Mounts to <div id=\"app\"> in index.html\n```\n\nThe app is a Vue 3 application. `app.component('LayoutDefault', Default)` registers the default layout component globally under the kebab-case name `layout-default`, which is exactly what `App.vue` resolves to dynamically.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Root component (`App.vue`)\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <component :is=\"layout\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </component>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nexport default {\n  name: 'App',\n  computed: {\n    layout() {\n      return `layout-${this.$route.meta.layout || 'default'}`\n    },\n  },\n}\n</script>\n```\n\n- The `<component :is=\"layout\">` tag is a **dynamic component** that renders whichever layout component is determined by the current route's metadata.\n- The computed `layout` reads `this.$route.meta.layout`. If the route defines `meta: { layout: 'default' }`, it becomes `layout-default`, which matches the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component.\n- Inside the layout wrapper, a `<RouterView />` renders the matched route's page component.\n\nThis pattern allows **per-route layout switching**: any route can define a different `meta.layout` to use a different layout component (e.g., `meta: { layout: 'empty' }` would render `<LayoutEmpty>`).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Router configuration (`src/router/index.js`)\n\n```js\nimport { createRouter, createWebHashHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport Home from '../views/Home.vue'\n\nconst history = createWebHashHistory()\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    component: () => import(/* webpackChunkName: \"about\" */ '../views/About.vue'),\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n]\n```\n\n- Uses **hash-based history** (`createWebHashHistory()`) – URLs look like `/#/about`.\n- Two routes:\n  - **`/` (Home)** – eagerly imported from `Home.vue`.\n  - **`/about` (About)** – **lazy-loaded** via a dynamic `import()`, which tells Vite to create a separate chunk (`about.[hash].js`) that is fetched only when the route is visited.\n- Both routes specify `meta: { layout: 'default' }`, so they both use the default layout.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Default layout (`src/layouts/default/Default.vue`)\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\nThe layout provides the **structural shell** for every page:\n- **`DefaultNav`** – a Bootstrap navbar with `RouterLink` items for Home and About, plus a responsive toggle.\n- **`<slot />`** – the outlet where `<RouterView />` content (the matched page component) is rendered.\n- **`DefaultFooter`** – a sticky footer at the bottom.\n\nThe layout also includes SCSS for a sticky footer pattern.\n\n---\n\n## How the About page is loaded\n\n1. **User navigates** to `/#/about` (or clicks the \"About\" link in `DefaultNav.vue`).\n\n2. **Vue Router matches** the `/about` path and triggers the lazy `import()`:\n   ```js\n   component: () => import('../views/About.vue')\n   ```\n   This causes the browser to fetch the separate chunk `about.[hash].js` **on demand** (route-level code-splitting).\n\n3. **App.vue** re-evaluates its computed `layout` property. Since the About route has `meta: { layout: 'default' }`, the dynamic component resolves to `<LayoutDefault>`.\n\n4. **LayoutDefault** renders its template:\n   - `DefaultNav` (the navigation bar with Home/About links)\n   - `<slot />` – the outlet for `<RouterView />`\n   - `DefaultFooter`\n\n5. **Inside the slot**, Vue Router renders the lazy-loaded `About.vue` component:\n   ```vue\n   <template>\n     <div class=\"container\">\n       <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n     </div>\n   </template>\n   ```\n\n6. The result is a fully rendered page: **navbar → \"This is the about page\" heading → footer**, all wrapped in the default layout's shell.\n\n---\n\n### Summary diagram\n\n```\nindex.html\n └─ <div id=\"app\">\n     └─ App.vue\n         └─ <component :is=\"'layout-default'\">\n              └─ LayoutDefault.vue\n                   ├─ DefaultNav.vue   (Home | About links)\n                   ├─ <slot>\n                   │    └─ <RouterView>\n                   │         └─ About.vue  (lazy-loaded chunk)\n                   └─ DefaultFooter.vue\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1673, "prompt_tokens": 9056, "total_tokens": 10729, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 455, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8192}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8192, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 864}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "3d97da48-198b-49f7-822d-930b63df277f", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea774-f149-7f40-b68d-b449ccbe09c9-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9056, "output_tokens": 1673, "total_tokens": 10729, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8192}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 455}}}}]}}}
